config SMC
	tristate "SMC socket protocol family"
	depends on INET && INFINIBAND
	help
	  SMC-R provides a "sockets over RDMA" solution making use of
	  RDMA over Converged Ethernet (RoCE) technology to upgrade
	  AF_INET TCP connections transparently.
	  The Linux implementation of the SMC-R solution is designed as
	  a separate socket family SMC.

	  Select this option if you want to run SMC socket applications

config SMC_DIAG
	tristate "SMC: socket monitoring interface"
	depends on SMC
	help
	  Support for SMC socket monitoring interface used by tools such as
	  smcss.

	  if unsure, say Y.

if SMC

config SMC_AUTO_FALLBACK
	bool "SMC: automatic fallback to TCP"
	default y
	help
	  Allow automatic fallback to TCP accroding to the pressure of SMC-R
	  handshake process.

	  If that's not what you except or unsure, say N.
endif
